PLANTS OF NE TENNESSEE
East Tennessee State University Herbarium

*Galax aphylla* L.
DIAPENSIACEAE

TENNESSEE. Johnson CO. Backbone Rock; cliffs on side
of rock on tunnel loop trail.

Moist woodland in moss and rich soil; shaded south
facing cliff 2200'; 36.5941, -81.8151

White flowering spikes; evergreen perennial with
rhizomes; basal leaves w/ flower stalks 1-2' tall. Many
flowers.

Species determination made using: Radford, A. E., Hales, H. E., & Bell,
C. R., (1968). Manual of the Vascular Flora of the Carolinas.
